parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks, such as loss of control, accidents, or even collapse of the frame.
symptoms: Excessive rust and corrosion on the frame
springs
and drive shaft
rust flakes coming off when pressure is applied
vibration on the steering while traveling at certain speeds
lurching when shifting into gear
frequent brake job replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the rear center bumper can lead to structural weakening, potentially causing safety issues, such as loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the rear center bumper
observed on multiple vehicles of the same model year.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire tread separation can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected loss of tire tread
often accompanied by a loud noise or vibration
while driving at moderate to high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient tire tread life can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: Excessive tire wear
reduced tire tread depth
and premature replacement of tires despite regular maintenance and proper inflation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Vibration and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The severe brake vibration can cause the loss of control on wet surfaces, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: Violent vibration of the front and rear of the vehicle
bouncing of the vehicle
inability to control the vehicle on wet surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warped Rotors and Brake Pads Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warped rotors and failed brake pads can cause the brake vibration, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Severe brake vibration
turned rotors
new brake pads do not resolve the issue
violent vibration of the front and rear of the vehicle.
